# SWOT Analysis

Strategic analysis canvas — map internal strengths & weaknesses
against external opportunities & threats.

## Config
flow = LR
spacing = 60

## Strengths
- [s1] Strong brand recognition {strength} {icon:⭐}
  Trusted by 50k+ users in the enterprise segment.
- [s2] Deep domain expertise {strength} {icon:🧠}
- [s3] Low customer acquisition cost {strength} {icon:💰}
- [s4] Proprietary data moat {strength} {icon:🔒}

## Weaknesses
- [w1] Slow release velocity {weakness} {icon:🐢}
  Currently shipping bi-monthly vs competitor weekly cadence.
- [w2] High churn in SMB segment {weakness} {icon:📉}
- [w3] Limited mobile experience {weakness} {icon:📱}
- [w4] Engineering team is understaffed {weakness} {icon:👥}

## Opportunities
- [o1] AI/LLM integration wave {opportunity} {icon:🤖} {glow}
  First-mover opportunity in the next 6 months.
- [o2] Enterprise compliance requirements {opportunity} {icon:📋}
- [o3] Partner ecosystem expansion {opportunity} {icon:🤝}
- [o4] International markets untapped {opportunity} {icon:🌍}

## Threats
- [t1] Well-funded competitor entering market {threat-swot} {icon:⚠️}
- [t2] Pricing pressure from open-source alternatives {threat-swot} {icon:💸}
- [t3] Data privacy regulation changes {threat-swot} {icon:⚖️}
- [t4] Key talent acquisition risk {threat-swot} {icon:🎯}

## Flow
s1 --> o1: leverage
s4 --> o2: advantage
w1 --> t1: risk amplifier
w4 --> t4: compounded risk
o1 --> w3: mitigate via AI
